eal with the new spells from the expansions and melee balancing.  What do you think the new CT and Inny were?  Yet the only solution to caster balancing is to nerf mages more.  Any caster balancing will hurt the guilds that adopted the philosophy that Melee/Healer's were the key to high end encounters.  So adjust, come up with new strategies.  You’re all complaining the high-end encounters are boring and monotonous anyway.<br>
<br>
The main complaint seems to be that it’s too “easy” to get the new mage summoned items.  I don’t hear anyone complaining that it’s too easy to get complete heal for clerics, or clarity for chanters.  Those spells are seen as those classes “defining” elements, so no one bats an eye.  Do they have a massive impact on end-game encounters?  Of course.  In the same patch that introduced focus items, wizards got innate critical hits.  You think that isn’t going to have a massive impact on their damage?  I’m not saying they should get that ability taken away.  I think its very logical that warriors, masters of melee, get critical hits and wizards, masters of damage casting, get critical blasts.  However, mages are supposedly the masters of summoning; isn’t the ability to summon focus items just as logical?  Also in that patch enchanters had most of their high-level mez spells upgraded.  Tell me that doesn’t change fighting dynamics.  But everyone says “Hey, great. Now all our chanters are even more useful”.  How many hours of camping or xp did wizards and chanters have to put in for their upgrades?  Yet everyone is pissed off that mage’s didn’t have to work their butts off to become useful.  Mage’s get an ability that actually makes them useful and unique, and immediately everyone jumps all over them.  Throw the guys a bone.  When have you ever seen someone shout, “group looking for mage”?  Try playing a mage until 54 (top of the line summoning spells), begging for groups, usually not getting them, then going off to solo.  On the off chance you do get a group, you’re job consists of sitting, hitting pet attack, and summoning mod rods for the “useful” classes.  Spend hours sitting LFG in Velks and watch the first cleric that zones in get a group instantly.  Then tell me it’s too easy to get these new items.<br>
